description:
Intrepido was a long lasting italian comic magazine, containing stories of various authors. It started in 1935 and lasted until 1996. From 1963 to 1982 it was a variety magazine, with comics and other contents. From 1982 to 1992 it was renamed Intrepido Sport, and was mainly a sports magazine. It returned to publish comics from 1992 till the closure, in 1997.

Note: Issues in this series are not numbered continously. The number here used is: YYYYNN, for example 199201 is number 1 of 1992.
name: Intrepido

deck: The second volume of Dave Stevens' Rocketeer blasts off with an all-new selection of great stories by some of the best in the biz!
description:
The second volume of Dave Stevens' Rocketeer blasts off with an all-new selection of great stories by some of the best in the biz! This issue starts off with a bang as Cliff finds himself in a dogfight, followed by a screening of everyone's favorite cartoon character, and ending on a high-note with a lovely and somewhat familiar story-plus a gorgeous pin-up by Arthur Adams! That's 25-count 'em, TWO FIVE-pages of topnotch comics!

Collected in Rocketeer Adventures 2.
name: Rocketeer Adventures 2
